com.austinv11.collectiveframework.minecraft.config

Class ConfigLoadEvent

  • java.lang.Object
    • cpw.mods.fml.common.eventhandler.Event
      • com.austinv11.collectiveframework.minecraft.config.ConfigLoadEvent
  • Direct Known Subclasses:
    ConfigLoadEvent.Init, ConfigLoadEvent.Post, ConfigLoadEvent.Pre

    public class ConfigLoadEvent
extends cpw.mods.fml.common.eventhandler.Event
    This is called when CollectiveFramework attempts to load a config. When a config is synced, it is called in two parts, PRE: Before the reload and POST: After the reload. The Init event is posted BEFORE a config is read (if it currently exists) NOTE: This is called on the MinecraftForge event bus
